https://guides.cocoapods.org/using/troubleshooting.html - CocoaPods docs

If you have no permission get the admin rights
Open the Terminal and write comand sudo su
You can check the version pod --version
If you have CocoaPods in you mac you cn delete it and reinstal for last version
$ gem uninstall cocoapods
$ gem install cocoapods

After build your project you shold tap the root folder and check in menu Services -> New Terminal at Folder
And wright: "pod update" command
Your project get needed dependencies for new Cocoapods in your mac
And then open your project in XCOode with white file .workspace extension
